text:
Riverside park: A northward view from a point on a line with West 75th Street, showing the marginal lands being filled preparatory to landscaping, and the New York Central Railroad tracks. The latter will be shifted to the graded bed seen in the foreground and later covered over by a concrete viaduct.

July 11, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Riverside Park - 75th Street (West).

text:
Squatters Colony, Camp Thomas Paine, Manhattan: A set of 3 views of this B.E.F. encampment of unemployed veterans on the Hudson River at the foot of West 75th Street. View No. 1 is northward across the New York Central Railroad tracks while Nos. 2 and 3 form a panoramic close-up. Across the background of all these views are the highlands of New Jersey.

September 29, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Squatters Colony - Camp Thomas Paine.
